</Procedure>
</Sect2>
<Sect2 Id="ToChooseAListItemKB">
<Title>To Select a List Item</Title>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>selecting: list item, with keyboard</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>keyboard: selecting a list item</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<Para>Some windows and dialog boxes display lists from which you
select options or settings.
</Para>
<OrderedList>
<ListItem Id="HIMGR.KEYB.item.76">
<Para>Press Tab to move the highlight to the list.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HIMGR.KEYB.item.77">
<Para>Press the arrow keys to move through the list.</Para>
<Para>To select more then one contiguous item in lists that allow you to do so,
press Shift+Down Arrow or Shift+Up Arrow.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HIMGR.KEYB.item.78">
<Para>Press Tab to move the highlight to the appropriate button
(such as OK), then press Return.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</OrderedList>
<Procedure>
<Title>See Also</Title>
<Step>
<ItemizedList Mark="&bull;" Role="tight">
<ListItem Id="HIMGR.KEYB.item.79">
<Para><Link Type="jump" Linkend="MovingKBFocus">Moving the Keyboard Focus</Link>
</Para>
</ListItem>
</ItemizedList>
<!-- MENU KEYBOARD NAVIGATION -->
</Step>
